### Managing <head> with next/head

The `Head` component lets you modify the `<head>` of a page:

```jsx
import Head from 'next/head';

export default function About() {
  return (
    <>
      <Head>
        <title>About Us | My Site</title>
        <meta name="description" content="Learn more about our company" />
        <meta property="og:title" content="About Us" />
      </Head>
      <h1>About Us</h1>
    </>
  );
}
```

### Optimized Images with next/image

The `Image` component provides automatic image optimization:

```jsx
import Image from 'next/image';

export default function Hero() {
  return (
    <Image
      src="/hero.jpg"
      alt="Hero banner"
      width={1200}
      height={600}
      priority
    />
  );
}
```

Benefits: lazy loading by default, responsive images, WebP format, proper sizing.

### Static Assets in public/

Files in `public/` are served at the root URL:

```
public/
  favicon.ico    -> /favicon.ico
  images/
    logo.png     -> /images/logo.png
  fonts/
    custom.woff2 -> /fonts/custom.woff2
```

Reference them with absolute paths: `/images/logo.png`.

### Custom Fonts with next/font

```jsx
import { Inter } from 'next/font/google';

const inter = Inter({ subsets: ['latin'] });

export default function Layout({ children }) {
  return (
    <html className={inter.className}>
      <body>{children}</body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

This self-hosts fonts with zero layout shift.

